<br>
a) I don't have enough screen space to have the map up all the time<br>
b) I don't *need* to have the map up all the time to successfully use it. I've been playing 3D games for a long, long time, and I can pretty much memorize a zone's layout after passing through it once. I only use the map in brief bursts just to see if I'm still on course or to briefly consult an area of the zone that I haven't been to before.<br>
<br>
Which makes the grey lines extraordinarily annoying because I have to take my mouse off of the map window, wait for about 3 seconds, and only then can I read the map. And if I put it up and take it back out, I've got to do this all over again. I'm sure you can edit the text file and change the line colors, but thus far I've been too lazy to get around to doing it. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://stathol.home.comcast.net/stathol/signature.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
